The paper deals with object pose estimation for robotics and augmented reality applications, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves physics simulation, which is also relevant to graphics (cs.GR). The approach involves optimization and search-based methods, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
